column5: The recent rain has made us have to change plans somewhat.  But that is how fishing goes.  Tournament anglers sometimes prefish and then can't get to their fish.  Ice fishing is really no different.  Safety is always the first priority but we don't just fish a spot out of convenience either.  We set out this morning on good safe ice with fish in the area and although the action wasn't fast and furious, we did catch a decent number of fish.  The biggest fish of the day was 11lbs.  Here are a few photos of some of today's fish.  Jeff
Sweet deal! Lots of pictures... I'd hate to see a fast and furious day!
ok so, i just finally pealed my tounge back up off the floor.. lol nice fish!
Nice going. I'll be out there tomorrow and Wednesday gunning for some beauties like that.
WOW, you boys got BOQ dialed in nice, love the reports guys, keep up the good work
Thanks!  The bite was similar this morning.  I caught 3 and missed one but packed up by 9:45.  Jeff
Just got back. Iced one nice fish about 5 and a half, but that wind was a killer.  I'll be back at 'er tomorrow evening.

Perfect conditions today.  We had a great flurry of action at dusk.  Went 5 for 7 with the biggest coming in around 7 pounds.  Of course the camera was dead.  Fish came on buckshots and cleos with shiners, and jigheads with 4-5" suckers.
What are you danging aboot son???... go get'em!!!... trim yer nose hairs before ya go, it's good luck yanno!
